                            <comment id="51015" author="bfaccini" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2013 02:46:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank&apos;s for the info/link Bobijam, I am sorry but I found this late yesterday evening and missed more time to find if it was already addressed ...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="51009" author="bobijam" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2013 22:26:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;b1_8 patch is tracked at &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/5129&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/5129&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50976" author="bfaccini" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2013 10:56:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Got the same issue/error when manually building latest Lustre 1.8 sources (1.8.8.60) from latest 2.6.18 Kernel sources (2.6.18-348.el5.src), but with &quot;lustre/include/lprocfs_status.h&quot; include file and same pre-processor statement :&lt;br/&gt;
567	#ifdef HAVE_PROCFS_USERS		&lt;br/&gt;
568	#error proc_dir_entry-&amp;gt;deleted is conflicted with proc_dir_entry-&amp;gt;pde_users		&lt;br/&gt;
569	#endif&lt;br/&gt;
Same fix (remove statement&apos;s 3 lines!) works just fine ...&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="50869" author="bergwolf" created="Sun, 20 Jan 2013 22:28:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch landed on master. We can close this. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
